Abuja – The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission have said its operatives stormed the ongoing presidential primary elections of the major opposition political party, the Peoples Democratic Party at the Moshood Kashimawo Abiola National Stadium in Abuja to monitor delegates inducement and financial malpractices. The anti-graft agency’s Public Relations Officer, Wilson Uwujaren, who disclosed this said, “Our operatives are at the ongoing PDP presidential primary elections at the MKO Abiola Stadium to monitor the exercise, and most especially, to check delegates inducement and other financial malpractices”. Recall that operatives of the EFCC stormed the venue of the ongoing PDP’s presidential primary elections in Abuja following reports of alleged vote buying and bribing of delegates at the event. More details later… By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Accreditation of the National delegates for the presidential primary election of the Peoples Democratic Party is underway. The presidential primary is being held at the MKO Abiola International Stadium, Abuja. The PUNCH reports that no fewer than 811 of delegates from the 774… In "Top Stories" .... As protests mar governorship primaries By Chibuike Nwabuko ABUJA - Former Governor of Anambra State and presidential hopeful, Peter Obi, has dropped out of the presidential race of the PDP amid talks with the Rabiu-Kwankwaso-led New Nigeria Peoples Party, the Labour Party and the Social Democratic Party, This is… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) National Convention Organizing Committee (NCOC), Senator David Mark has assured that arrangements have been made for a hitch free exercise on Saturday (28/5/22). This was contained in a statement signed by his Media Adviser, Paul… In "Top Stories"